solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    long long repairCars(vector<int>& ranks, int cars) {
        long long left = 1, right = 1LL * *min_element(ranks.begin(), ranks.end()) * cars * cars;
        while (left < right) {
            long long mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            long long total = 0;
            for (int r : ranks) {
                total += static_cast<long long>(sqrt(mid / r));
                if (total >= cars) break;
            }
            if (total >= cars) right = mid;
            else left = mid + 1;
        }
        return left;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log(max_time))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Binary search on the minimum time. For each candidate time, compute how many cars each mechanic can repair (sqrt(time/rank)) and sum them. The search space is bounded by the slowest mechanic repairing all cars alone.

